To create a C# software that reads Iranian license plates from an image and writes it into a text file, you can use Optical Character Recognition (OCR) libraries like Tesseract. Tesseract is an open-source OCR engine that can recognize multiple languages, including Persian (Farsi) which is used in Iranian license plates.

Here are the steps to create a C# software using the Tesseract library:

1. Install Tesseract NuGet package
Open your Visual Studio and create a new C# project. Right-click on your project and select "Manage NuGet Packages". Then search for "Tesseract" and install the package named "Tesseract".

2. Install the additional required packages:
Search for and install the following NuGet packages: 
    - Tesseract.Text.Xaml
    - System.Drawing.Common

3. Download Persian (Farsi) trained model
Download the Persian trained model for Tesseract from https://github.com/tesseract-ocr/tessdata/blob/master/fas.traineddata. Create a "tessdata" folder inside your project and put the downloaded file there.

4. Implement the OCR function
Add the following code to your project:

```csharp
using System;
using System.Drawing;
using System.IO;
using Tesseract;

namespace LicensePlateReader
{
    class Program
    {
        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            string imagePath = "path/to/your/image.jpg"; // Add the image path
            string outputTextFile = "output.txt"; // Output text file

            string licensePlate = ReadLicensePlate(imagePath);
            WriteTextToFile(licensePlate, outputTextFile);

            Console.WriteLine("The license plate is: " + licensePlate);
        }

        static string ReadLicensePlate(string imagePath)
        {
            string extractedText = "";

            using (var engine = new TesseractEngine(@"./tessdata", "fas", EngineMode.Default))
            {
                using (var img = Pix.LoadFromFile(imagePath))
                {
                    using (var page = engine.Process(img))
                    {
                        extractedText = page.GetText();
                        float confidence = page.GetMeanConfidence();

                        Console.WriteLine("Confidence: " + (confidence * 100) + "%");
                    }
                }
            }

            return extractedText;
        }

        static void WriteTextToFile(string text, string filePath)
        {
            File.WriteAllText(filePath, text);
        }
    }
}
```

Replace "path/to/your/image.jpg" with the path to the image containing the Iranian license plate. The code above reads the license plate, writes the OCR-result text into a file, and outputs the license plate information to the console.

5. Run the software
Build and run the software. The Iranian license plate from the image will be read and the result will be written into the "output.txt" file. The console will show the confidence level and the license plate number.

